  "market_context": "Daily bias turned bearish after price swept previous day high but failed to close above it. New York session approached with a marked hourly fair value gap near midnight open, setting up a short entry.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept previous day high, closed back inside the range, triggering a bearish next-day model bias; an hourly FVG formed near NY open, confirmed by a 5-minute FVG for entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On daily chart, analyst observed price swept previous day high but failed to close above it, establishing bearish daily bias via Next Day Model.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to hourly chart, marked midnight open and identified a fair value gap (FVG) forming as price entered New York kill zone.",
    "Step 3: Switched to 5-minute chart, located a confluence FVG at 1.25501–1.25900, used as point of interest for entry.",
    "Step 4: Set stop loss above the recent swing high (1.26155), targeted 2R initially and deeper swing low (~1.25100) for extended move."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target successfully; price continued lower toward deeper swing low.",
  "lessons": "Next Day Model provides reliable intraday bias when price sweeps PDH/PDL but fails to close beyond it; FVGs on HTF and LTF aligned during NY kill zone offer high-probability entries with tight risk.",
